commit_message:
[DNM] Convert JSON: assertion strings

With input assertion:

openstack_user: test
openstack_groups: JSON:{"name":"group1","domain":{"name":"xxx"}};JSON:{"name":"group2","domain":{"name":"yyy"}}

(notice use of "name" and "domain" with object instead of
"group_name"/"domain_name")

and rules file:

[
    {
        "local": [
            {
                "user": {
                    "name": "{0}"
                }
            },
            {
                "groups": "{1}"
            }
        ],
        "remote": [
            {
                "type": "openstack_user"
            },
            {
                "type": "openstack_groups"
            }
        ]
    }
]

the mapping engine can now process complex group objects:

$ keystone-manage mapping_engine --input ~/input.txt --rules ~/rules.json
{
  "group_ids": [],
  "user": {
    "domain": {
      "id": "Federated"
    },
    "type": "ephemeral",
    "name": "test"
  },
  "projects": [],
  "group_names": [
    {
      "domain": {
        "name": "xxx"
      },
      "name": "group1"
    },
    {
      "domain": {
        "name": "yyy"
      },
      "name": "group2"
    }
  ]
}

